<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - OIL COOLER and FILTER HOUSING - Removal - Oil Filter Base
        Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>Oil Filter Base Assembly</title>
        <figure id="f2650903" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D1339.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 333. Oil filter cap</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, do not allow engine fluids to stay on your skin. Clean skin
                    and nails with hand cleaner and soap and water. Wash or dispose of clothing or rags containing
                    engine fluids.
                </para>
            </warning>
            <note>
                <para>Engine fluids (oil, fuel, and coolant) are a threat to the environment. Recycle or dispose of
                    engine fluids according to local regulations. Never put engine fluids in the trash, on the ground,
                    in sewers or other bodies of water.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil filter cap and filter element. Discard filter element and oil filter cap seal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650904" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13108.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 334. Oil filter housing mounting bolts (4)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove four M8 x 75 mounting bolts from the oil filter housing and remove housing. Discard
                the filter housing base seal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650905" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13109.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 335. Oil filter return tube</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the oil filter return tube, remove M5 x 18 lockscrew and turn tube
                counterclockwise and lift up.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard oil filter return tube gasket.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Oil filter base does not have to be removed in order to remove the oil cooler assembly.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650906" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13110.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 336. EGR cooler coolant supply port cover bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove EGR cooler coolant supply port cover bolts (2) and remove cover and discard seal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650907" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13111.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 337. Oil filter base bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove eight mounting bolts from oil filter base assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350906" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D1306.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 338. Removing oil filter base assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift oil filter base assembly off oil cooler cover assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard gasket.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
